      "writtenOn": "2020-08-10T02:05:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "sk_sp and SkString will definitely each cause a mountain of fix-its. I definitely want to do them separately, and TBH I wasn\u0027t sure whether we\u0027d want to do them at all. SkString\u0027s doc comments in particular encourage users to treat it as a value type (\"Uses reference counting to make string assignments and copies very fast with no extra RAM cost\"). sk_sp is everywhere and is treated like a value type pretty much universally as well. I don\u0027t have a frame of reference for whether the sk_sp virtual calls and atomic incs/decs cost a meaningful amount of perf in the aggregate.",
      "parentUuid": "a78e136f_9e57764f",
      "revId": "26d195d9324ee954da24ce83299a41b28533a99c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
